RACE.FOOTNOTES: MALTESE FALCON (IRE) secured the rail exiting the chute and rated kindly well within range, took advantage of an inside path and responded to a right handed ask in mid stretch, forged through to take over near the sixteenth marker then kicked clear under steady hand encouragement. AGENCY grabbed command soon after the start and set a rated pace towards the rail, came under coaxing past the quarter pole, straightened away two wide and under a drive past the three sixteenths, dug in when confronted past mid stretch, kept on gamely but was nipped for the place. JUSTIN'S LEGACY , fractious behind the gate, was loaded without his rider, prompted the pace two wide, shifted three wide pursuing into the lane then gave way grudgingly between foes. KID AZTECA rated towards the inside and in range, eased out then steadied briefly near the five sixteenths, moved back in through the final furlong and kept on with effort. HENRY Q stalked the pace three wide, shifted four wide for the drive and faded late. SMART MO was taken in leaving the chute and saved ground, crept up past the five sixteenths, briefly steadied soon after, remained inside for the drive and lacked a bit of room near the sixteenth pole. ZALAMO (FR) broke outward, settled early while inside, angled six wide for the drive but failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE KEY IS UNITY rated six wide off the early three way battle, dropped in a path and rolled up five wide nearing the quarter pole, assumed command soon into the lane eagerly drew away under a solid drive. SNAPP DADDY bobbled at the break and bumped with a rival, regrouped to save ground, edged up nearing the turn, angled four wide to work between runners into the lane, straightened away to give willing chase and out kicked MT. ZEROR for the place. MT. ZEROR vied between rivals early, chased the leader three wide nearing the stretch, came back on between foes in mid stretch and kept on trying to the inside of SNAPP DADDY. WHISKEY VISION , off the early pace, came out mid turn, circled six wide with a run into the stretch then flattened out through the final furlong. BYE EVERYBODY roughed badly at the break and found himself far back after a quarter mile, continued well off the pace mid turn, saved ground into the stretch, came out for the final furlong and finished with good energy. MY BROTHER MIKE dueled inside rivals, moved away mid turn, was overwhelmed by the winner soon into the lane and tired. HARD TIMES , rated between rivals leaving the far turn, checked when in tight near the quarter pole, came three wide for the drive but lacked a solid recovery. BLUEGRASS RYDER bobbled at the break, raced between runners around the turn, shifted out well wide in upper stretch but failed to rally. LA'OCH ALOYSIUS bore out the break and bumped with a rival, straightened and rolled up towards the rail, stalked the leaders leaving the far turn, chased to the quarter pole and faded. DIAMONDS PREFERRED broke awkwardly, raced off the pace and four wide past the quarter pole, angled wider for the drive but failed to make an impact. MISSING THEM vied three deep, failed to keep pace past the five sixteenths and faltered. IT WAS A GOOD DAY , well wide with early pursuit, dropped back around the turn.
